"{\"statement\": \"Task: Given an arbitrary number of arrays, create a function that returns a single array generated by alternately appending elements from the passed-in arguments. If one of the arrays is shorter than the others, the result should be padded with `nil`s.\\n\\nInput: The input consists of an arbitrary number of arrays, where each array can contain any type of element. The input arrives from standard input.\\n\\nOutput: The output is a single array generated by alternately appending elements from the passed-in arguments. If one of the arrays is shorter than the others, the result should be padded with `nil`s.\\n\\nConstraints: None specified.\", \"editorial\": \"\", \"tag\": \"['Data structures']\", \"difficulties\": \"EASY\", \"source\": \"codewars\", \"url\": \"https://www.codewars.com/kata/523d2e964680d1f749000135\", \"sample_test_cases\": [{\"input\": [[1, 2, 3], [\"c\", \"d\", \"e\"]], \"output\": [[1, \"c\", 2, \"d\", 3, \"e\"]]}, {\"input\": [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5]], \"output\": [[1, 4, 2, 5, 3, null]]}, {\"input\": [[1, 2], [3, 4, 5]], \"output\": [[1, 3, 2, 4, null, 5]]}, {\"input\": [[null], [null, null], [null, null, null]], \"output\": [[null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null]]}, {\"input\": [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6], [7, 8, 9]], \"output\": [[1, 4, 7, 2, 5, 8, 3, 6, 9]]}, {\"input\": [[]], \"output\": [[]]}]}"